gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 108, Lakers 106
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Lakers, 108-106. Anthony Edwards led Minnesota with 31 points (10-23 FG) as Naz Reid (21 points, five rebounds) and Rudy Gobert (13 points, 13 rebounds) totaled 34 points. Anthony Davis totaled 33 points, 17 rebounds, eight assists, four steals, and two blocks while LeBron James added 26 points, three rebounds, and six assists. The Timberwolves improve to 24-7 on the year (14-1 at home, most home wins in the Western Conference) as the Lakers move to 17-16.
